arts.ttl: Vincent Kompany critical of Bayern Munich’s finish in 4-3 win over Holstein Kiel
arts.sum: Bayern Munich ’s overall dominance over Holstein Kiel was not at all represented in the final 4-3 scoreline, but Kiel’s two late goals made it a cagey ending for the Rekordmeister . The second half goals from Kiel’s Finn Porath and two from Steven Skrzybski in the 91st and 93rd minute really cut into Bayern’s four-goal lead and very nearly sparked what would have been the most embarrassing bottle job from Bayern had Kiel found a fourth.

arts.ttl: European football: record-breaking Kane hits double as Bayern beat Kiel 4-3
arts.sum: England captain has most goals in 50 Bundesliga games Dortmund claim nervous 2-1 victory over Heidenheim The Bundesliga leaders Bayern Munich conceded three goals in the second half but beat Holstein Kiel 4-3 on Saturday, with the striker Harry Kane scoring twice to set a league record for most goals after 50 games. Bayern eased off in the second half and let in three goals in the last 28 minutes in a shaky second-half performance, but held on for the win that opened a nine-point lead at the top. arts.ttl: Harry Kane's double on 50th appearance helps Bayern Munich survive late Holstein Kiel comeback
arts.sum: Harry Kane marked his 50th Bundesliga appearance with a brace as Bundesliga leaders Bayern Munich held off a spirited late fightback from Holstein Kiel in a seven-goal thriller at the Allianz Arena. Kiel's best opportunity of the half fell to Lewis Holtby, whose close-range effort was cleared off the line by Minjae Kim. As the first half drew to a close, Kane doubled Bayern's lead with a powerful header from Kingsley Coman's cross, sending the hosts into the break with a deserved cushion.
